<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,834,2013]" box="[151,1155,834,859]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,834,859]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">Description.</emphasis>
Body length (from apex of vertex to tip of forewings): male 8.8 mm (n = 
<number box="[1124,1137,834,858]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="1.0">1</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,834,2013]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis box="[201,331,870,894]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">Coloration.</emphasis>
General color blackish brown (
<figureCitation box="[706,891,870,894]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 64" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1865,1888]" captionTargetBox="[167,1425,208,1821]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1844]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 64. Adult of Macrocixius species. 53, 57, 61. M. giganteus. (53) Habitus, dorsal view; (57) Habitus, lateral view; (61) Face, ventral view. 54, 58, 62. M. grossus. (54) Habitus, dorsal view; (58) Habitus, lateral view; (62) Face, ventral view. 55, 59, 63. M. rarimaculatus. (55) Habitus, dorsal view; (59) Habitus, lateral view; (63) Face, ventral view. 56, 60, 64. M. unispinus. (56) Habitus, dorsal view; (60) Habitus, lateral view; (64) Face, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216904/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
Figs 
<number box="[767,844,870,894]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="56.6">56, 60</number>
, 
<number box="[859,891,870,894]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="64.0">64</number>
</figureCitation>
). Eyes yellowish brown alternating with black brown. Ocelli dull yellow. Face black brown, base and lateral margin deeply brown, areas around both ends of frontoclypeal suture with glassily yellow markings. Pronotum generally yellowish brown, area beside median carina and posterior margin of eyes black brown. Mesonotum black brown. Forewing colorless, hyaline, spreading with small dark brown markings on apical area, costal area and clavus area; stigma blackish brown; strip between bases of CuP and PCu black brown; yellow alternating with black brown on basal half of veins, apical half of veins mostly black brown. 
<collectingCountry box="[387,443,1086,1110]" name="India" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">Hind</collectingCountry>
tarsi with platellae yellow. Abdomen blackish brown ventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,834,2013]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis box="[201,262,1123,1147]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">Head</emphasis>
. Median ocellus (
<figureCitation box="[463,550,1122,1146]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 52" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[176,1416,204,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1884]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 52. Macrocixius unispinus sp. nov. (40) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (41) Face, ventral view; (42) Forewing; (43) Male genitalia, lateral view; (44) Pygofer and genital styles, ventral view; (45) Anal segment, dorsal view; (46) Anal segment, caudal view; (47) Right genital styles, ventral view; (48) Connective, dorsocephalad view; (49) Aedeagus, right side; (50) Aedeagus, left side; (51) Aedeagus, dorsal view; (52) Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216903/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
Figs 
<number box="[520,550,1122,1146]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="41.64">41</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[563,592,1122,1146]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 64" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1865,1888]" captionTargetBox="[167,1425,208,1821]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1844]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 64. Adult of Macrocixius species. 53, 57, 61. M. giganteus. (53) Habitus, dorsal view; (57) Habitus, lateral view; (61) Face, ventral view. 54, 58, 62. M. grossus. (54) Habitus, dorsal view; (58) Habitus, lateral view; (62) Face, ventral view. 55, 59, 63. M. rarimaculatus. (55) Habitus, dorsal view; (59) Habitus, lateral view; (63) Face, ventral view. 56, 60, 64. M. unispinus. (56) Habitus, dorsal view; (60) Habitus, lateral view; (64) Face, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216904/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">64</figureCitation>
) on the peak of frontoclypeal suture. Vertex (
<figureCitation box="[1103,1191,1122,1146]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 52" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[176,1416,204,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1884]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 52. Macrocixius unispinus sp. nov. (40) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (41) Face, ventral view; (42) Forewing; (43) Male genitalia, lateral view; (44) Pygofer and genital styles, ventral view; (45) Anal segment, dorsal view; (46) Anal segment, caudal view; (47) Right genital styles, ventral view; (48) Connective, dorsocephalad view; (49) Aedeagus, right side; (50) Aedeagus, left side; (51) Aedeagus, dorsal view; (52) Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216903/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
Figs 
<number box="[1160,1191,1122,1146]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="40.56">40</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1202,1231,1122,1146]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 64" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1865,1888]" captionTargetBox="[167,1425,208,1821]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1844]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 64. Adult of Macrocixius species. 53, 57, 61. M. giganteus. (53) Habitus, dorsal view; (57) Habitus, lateral view; (61) Face, ventral view. 54, 58, 62. M. grossus. (54) Habitus, dorsal view; (58) Habitus, lateral view; (62) Face, ventral view. 55, 59, 63. M. rarimaculatus. (55) Habitus, dorsal view; (59) Habitus, lateral view; (63) Face, ventral view. 56, 60, 64. M. unispinus. (56) Habitus, dorsal view; (60) Habitus, lateral view; (64) Face, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216904/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">56</figureCitation>
) 1.3 X wider than long; subapical carina joins lateral carinae at apical 
<number box="[759,770,1158,1182]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[781,797,1158,1182]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="6.0">6</number>
; anterior margin slightly sinuous with middle archedly convex, posterior margin nearly trapezoidally concave; areolets before subapical carina concave, area behind subapical carina archedly concave; both two portions of median carina existing. Frons (
<figureCitation box="[1145,1233,1230,1254]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 52" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[176,1416,204,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1884]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 52. Macrocixius unispinus sp. nov. (40) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (41) Face, ventral view; (42) Forewing; (43) Male genitalia, lateral view; (44) Pygofer and genital styles, ventral view; (45) Anal segment, dorsal view; (46) Anal segment, caudal view; (47) Right genital styles, ventral view; (48) Connective, dorsocephalad view; (49) Aedeagus, right side; (50) Aedeagus, left side; (51) Aedeagus, dorsal view; (52) Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216903/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
Figs 
<number box="[1203,1233,1230,1254]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="41.64">41</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1247,1276,1230,1254]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 64" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1865,1888]" captionTargetBox="[167,1425,208,1821]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1844]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 64. Adult of Macrocixius species. 53, 57, 61. M. giganteus. (53) Habitus, dorsal view; (57) Habitus, lateral view; (61) Face, ventral view. 54, 58, 62. M. grossus. (54) Habitus, dorsal view; (58) Habitus, lateral view; (62) Face, ventral view. 55, 59, 63. M. rarimaculatus. (55) Habitus, dorsal view; (59) Habitus, lateral view; (63) Face, ventral view. 56, 60, 64. M. unispinus. (56) Habitus, dorsal view; (60) Habitus, lateral view; (64) Face, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216904/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">64</figureCitation>
) 1.2 X longer than wide; anterior margin concave into an obtuse angle. Rostrum relatively long, reaching apex of hind femur, subapical segment 1.3 X longer than apical segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,834,2013]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis box="[201,510,1339,1363]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">Pronotum and mesonotum.</emphasis>
Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[649,740,1338,1362]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 52" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[176,1416,204,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1884]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 52. Macrocixius unispinus sp. nov. (40) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (41) Face, ventral view; (42) Forewing; (43) Male genitalia, lateral view; (44) Pygofer and genital styles, ventral view; (45) Anal segment, dorsal view; (46) Anal segment, caudal view; (47) Right genital styles, ventral view; (48) Connective, dorsocephalad view; (49) Aedeagus, right side; (50) Aedeagus, left side; (51) Aedeagus, dorsal view; (52) Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216903/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
Figs 
<number box="[709,740,1338,1362]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="40.56">40</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[755,784,1338,1362]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 64" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1865,1888]" captionTargetBox="[167,1425,208,1821]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1844]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 64. Adult of Macrocixius species. 53, 57, 61. M. giganteus. (53) Habitus, dorsal view; (57) Habitus, lateral view; (61) Face, ventral view. 54, 58, 62. M. grossus. (54) Habitus, dorsal view; (58) Habitus, lateral view; (62) Face, ventral view. 55, 59, 63. M. rarimaculatus. (55) Habitus, dorsal view; (59) Habitus, lateral view; (63) Face, ventral view. 56, 60, 64. M. unispinus. (56) Habitus, dorsal view; (60) Habitus, lateral view; (64) Face, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216904/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">56</figureCitation>
) 1.3 X longer than vertex; intermediate carinae curving forward, vanishing near anterior margin of pronotum; both sides of median carina deeply concave; posterior margin concave, forming an obtuse angle. Mesonotum (
<figureCitation box="[812,905,1410,1434]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 52" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[176,1416,204,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1884]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 52. Macrocixius unispinus sp. nov. (40) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (41) Face, ventral view; (42) Forewing; (43) Male genitalia, lateral view; (44) Pygofer and genital styles, ventral view; (45) Anal segment, dorsal view; (46) Anal segment, caudal view; (47) Right genital styles, ventral view; (48) Connective, dorsocephalad view; (49) Aedeagus, right side; (50) Aedeagus, left side; (51) Aedeagus, dorsal view; (52) Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216903/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
Figs 
<number box="[874,905,1410,1434]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="40.56">40</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[921,950,1410,1434]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 64" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1865,1888]" captionTargetBox="[167,1425,208,1821]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1844]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 64. Adult of Macrocixius species. 53, 57, 61. M. giganteus. (53) Habitus, dorsal view; (57) Habitus, lateral view; (61) Face, ventral view. 54, 58, 62. M. grossus. (54) Habitus, dorsal view; (58) Habitus, lateral view; (62) Face, ventral view. 55, 59, 63. M. rarimaculatus. (55) Habitus, dorsal view; (59) Habitus, lateral view; (63) Face, ventral view. 56, 60, 64. M. unispinus. (56) Habitus, dorsal view; (60) Habitus, lateral view; (64) Face, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216904/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">56</figureCitation>
) 1.7 X longer than pronotum and vertex combined; lateral carinae slightly sinuous, inner sides of them with fine short striations, median carina vanishing on posteromedian area.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,834,2013]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis box="[201,276,1520,1543]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">Wings.</emphasis>
Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[416,508,1518,1542]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 52" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[176,1416,204,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1884]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 52. Macrocixius unispinus sp. nov. (40) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (41) Face, ventral view; (42) Forewing; (43) Male genitalia, lateral view; (44) Pygofer and genital styles, ventral view; (45) Anal segment, dorsal view; (46) Anal segment, caudal view; (47) Right genital styles, ventral view; (48) Connective, dorsocephalad view; (49) Aedeagus, right side; (50) Aedeagus, left side; (51) Aedeagus, dorsal view; (52) Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216903/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
Figs 
<number box="[477,508,1518,1542]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="42.56">42</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[525,601,1518,1542]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 64" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1865,1888]" captionTargetBox="[167,1425,208,1821]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1844]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 64. Adult of Macrocixius species. 53, 57, 61. M. giganteus. (53) Habitus, dorsal view; (57) Habitus, lateral view; (61) Face, ventral view. 54, 58, 62. M. grossus. (54) Habitus, dorsal view; (58) Habitus, lateral view; (62) Face, ventral view. 55, 59, 63. M. rarimaculatus. (55) Habitus, dorsal view; (59) Habitus, lateral view; (63) Face, ventral view. 56, 60, 64. M. unispinus. (56) Habitus, dorsal view; (60) Habitus, lateral view; (64) Face, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216904/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
56, 
<number box="[572,601,1518,1542]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="60.0">60</number>
</figureCitation>
) 
<date box="[621,667,1518,1542]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
<number box="[621,635,1518,1542]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="3.0">3</number>
X
</date>
longer than wide; fork Sc+ 
<collectingCountry box="[1000,1036,1518,1542]" name="Poland" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">RP</collectingCountry>
distad of fork CuA 
<number box="[1277,1286,1518,1542]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="1.0">1</number>
+CuA 
<number box="[1359,1373,1518,1542]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="2.0">2</number>
, fork PCu+A 
<number box="[240,249,1554,1578]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="1.0">1</number>
distad of center of clavus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,834,2013]" box="[201,1301,1590,1617]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis box="[201,261,1594,1617]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">Legs.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[268,324,1593,1617]" name="India" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibia with 
<number box="[444,458,1593,1617]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="4.0">4</number>
lateral spines; chaetotaxy of hind tarsi: 
<number box="[905,918,1593,1617]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="8.0">8</number>
/ 
<number box="[929,969,1593,1617]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="9.2">9, 2</number>
nd hind tarsus with 
<number box="[1177,1191,1593,1617]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="4.0">4</number>
platellae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,834,2013]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1437,151,716]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="288" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis box="[201,314,1629,1653]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[430,564,1629,1653]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 52" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1905,1928]" captionTargetBox="[176,1416,204,1865]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,1884]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 52. Macrocixius unispinus sp. nov. (40) Head and thorax, dorsal view; (41) Face, ventral view; (42) Forewing; (43) Male genitalia, lateral view; (44) Pygofer and genital styles, ventral view; (45) Anal segment, dorsal view; (46) Anal segment, caudal view; (47) Right genital styles, ventral view; (48) Connective, dorsocephalad view; (49) Aedeagus, right side; (50) Aedeagus, left side; (51) Aedeagus, dorsal view; (52) Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216903/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="285">
Figs 
<number box="[490,564,1629,1653]" pageId="8" pageNumber="285" value="43.44">43, 44</number>
</figureCitation>
