<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="288" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,716]" pageId="11" pageNumber="288">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,317,512,536]" pageId="11" pageNumber="288">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[658,803,513,536]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Macrocixius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giganteus">
<emphasis box="[658,803,513,536]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="288">M. giganteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the main differences are as follows: (
<number box="[1229,1241,511,535]" pageId="11" pageNumber="288" value="1.0">1</number>
) forewing of this new species with fewer dark markings; (
<number box="[608,623,548,572]" pageId="11" pageNumber="288" value="2.0">2</number>
) the spines on the left side of the aedeagus differ from the latter in size, direction and position; (
<number box="[423,437,583,607]" pageId="11" pageNumber="288" value="3.0">3</number>
) the longest spine on right side of aedeagus about 
<date box="[1019,1061,583,608]" pageId="11" pageNumber="288">
<number box="[1019,1033,583,607]" pageId="11" pageNumber="288" value="2.0">2</number>
X
</date>
longer than the shortest one, not crossing dorsal margin of aedeagus to left; (
<number box="[661,676,620,644]" pageId="11" pageNumber="288" value="4.0">4</number>
) flagellum of this new species with one short spine on the dorsal margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[201,1428,692,716]" pageId="11" pageNumber="288" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,716]" box="[201,1428,692,716]" pageId="11" pageNumber="288">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,335,692,716]" pageId="11" pageNumber="288">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is derived from the Latin words “ 
<taxonomicName box="[834,942,693,716]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Macrocixius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unispinus">
<emphasis box="[834,942,693,716]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="288">unispinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, which refers to flagellum with one spine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
